Disabled regression test for issue #483: variables declared inside a loop are not re-initialised to null on each iteration.

Currently, .NET only zero-initialises locals once at method entry, so a `let x: string;` inside a loop retains whatever value was assigned to it on a previous iteration. Expected behaviour is that the implicit null initialiser is re-applied at the top of each iteration: i=0/1/2 should all print "x not set".

Re-enable by deleting this `disabled` file once the compiler emits a re-initialisation for loop-scoped locals without an explicit initialiser.
